reviews_data.review_text: Best coffee spot in all of charlotte

Excellent spot for coffee. The drinks are always smooth and full of flavor, but what really makes this place special is the people. The staff are genuinely friendly and make you feel right at home every time you walk in. Everything is clean and comfortable, and it’s the kind of café you end up wanting to hang around in a little longer than planned. Easily one of my favorite coffee shops in the area.

reviews_data.review_text: I stopped by Qahwah House and ordered a chai — it was excellent! Perfectly balanced with rich spices and a smooth finish, easily one of the best chai teas I’ve had in Charlotte. The café has a warm, inviting atmosphere with plenty of seating, making it a great place to relax or meet with friends. The staff were welcoming and attentive, which made the experience even better. I’m looking forward to coming back to try more of their drinks and pastries.

Qahwah House is easily one of the best spots in Charlotte. The coffee is rich and flavorful, and they use authentic Yemeni coffee beans with an incredible story behind them. You can really taste the difference compared to regular coffee shops. The atmosphere is warm and inviting, and the staff is welcoming and happy to share the history and culture behind what they serve. A unique experience you won’t find anywhere else. I’ll definitely be coming back.

reviews_data.review_text: Came here to try a new coffee shop. Was really impressed with the atmosphere. The barista was really helpful going over the options. I would highly recommend the strawberry cheesecake, brown sugar latte, and the refreshers. Will be coming back again!

Everything at Qahwah House Charlotte was incredible! The Yemeni iced latte was bold, creamy, and perfectly spiced. The croissant was flaky and buttery with a hint of sweetness, and the savory pastry was fresh and flavorful. Even the espresso was smooth and rich. Great vibes, amazing flavor—highly recommend! 🌟☕🥐
Everything is always so fresh and delicious!!

I tried these guys this week & was so impressed that I’ve since ordered from them 3X’s in total, ordering multiple items each time bc it was seriously THE BEST COFFEE I have EVER HAD & I needed to know if everything else was THAT amazing!
I’ll be visiting in person ASAP.

Here’s what I’ve had 🫣😆

Drinks:
________________________
Pistachio Hot Latte:  3X’s - The quality doesn’t quit!! Smooth, perfectly balanced flavor.
I tried another coffee house’s Pistachio Latte bc Qahwah was my first - all Pistachio Lattes are not made the same. Backyard Brew assaulted me at the first sip, (crushed pistachios throughout that created an awkward experience of feeling like you’re chewing trail mix & refuse to swallow before taking a sip of your drink 🤮).

Adeni Chai:  Amazing. Everything you expect from a Chai Latte, kicked up a notch. Bonus points for being able to control sugar levels.

Strawberry Matcha:  So good, so so good.
High quality and perfectly earthy without being overly sweet from artificial flavors. Mine did not have the layered effect of green matcha atop bright and pink melded strawberry cream, but it was delivered & it’s hot out here so they lost zero points in my book!

Mango Refresher:  Good. Comparably the quality is nice, but I could taste that it was flavored with mango syrup, reminiscent of when you order a flavored sweat tea. Maybe a teaspoon of tiny bits of mango floating on top.

Food:
__________________________
Pistachio Milk Cake:  Flavor was everything. Think pistachio tres leche. It was SLIGHTLY too moist, even for what it is - did NOT take from the experience though.

Yemen Chocolate:  Cute little gold dust on top, the price is more than fair considering it’s literally “Dubai Chocolate” - which I don’t enjoy because of the texture. The chocolate was of great quality, the pistachios were shaved into what reminds me of fried rice noodles. If you like Dubai Chocolate, you’ll enjoy. 😊

Triple Chocolate Cake:  DECADENNNTT. Top tier quality! I keep referring to quality but this place exudes it - made even more surprising bc it’s a chain. ⛓️‍💥 It isn’t huge, but because of    its richness, can be shared between ~2-3 of even the largest fatties! Velvety smooth,  thick mousse meets perfectly balanced, light and yet dense, sponge cake - Signed, sealed, & delivered in an exquisitely, complementary dark chocolate coating.

Chocolate Cappuccino Cake:  Needs work.
The cake was too dense and very dry. The icing was slightly “crusty” - not enough moisture and the flavor was missing that rich espresso flavor. It could have been stale, but I think it’s more likely that the recipe is struggling to retain moisture because it’s vegan.

All in all - will be back. I don’t even like sweets, but I’m committed now & am excited to try the desserts that pay homage to the Yemen culture! 😊

I absolutely LOVE Qahwah House: the vibrant atmosphere, well designed interior - we loved sitting on the sofa with moveable arm rests that lined the back wall, beautiful servers and baristas. It was so nice to meet the cheerful owner Sulaiman!

As someone with a dairy allergy I was so surprised to see they had vegan chocolate cake (made with almond and coconut milk). My friend and I came for dessert - I ordered the chocolate cake and he got the pistachio dream dessert and a cold Mofawar latte (with a dash of fragrant cardamom). We both greatly enjoyed what we ordered.

Another time I came and got their delicious peppermint tea. Highly recommend their tea, coffee, and desserts/pastries!

I’ll be visiting in person ASAP.

Here’s what I’ve had 🫣😆

Drinks:
________________________
Pistachio Hot Latte:  3X’s - The quality doesn’t quit!! Smooth, perfectly balanced flavor.
I tried another coffee house’s Pistachio Latte bc Qahwah was my first - all Pistachio Lattes are not made the same. Backyard Brew assaulted me at the first sip, (crushed pistachios throughout that created an awkward experience of feeling like you’re chewing trail mix & refuse to swallow before taking a sip of your drink 🤮).

Adeni Chai:  Amazing. Everything you expect from a Chai Latte, kicked up a notch. Bonus points for being able to control sugar levels.

Strawberry Matcha:  So good, so so good.
High quality and perfectly earthy without being overly sweet from artificial flavors. Mine did not have the layered effect of green matcha atop bright and pink melded strawberry cream, but it was delivered & it’s hot out here so they lost zero points in my book!

Mango Refresher:  Good. Comparably the quality is nice, but I could taste that it was flavored with mango syrup, reminiscent of when you order a flavored sweat tea. Maybe a teaspoon of tiny bits of mango floating on top.

Food:
__________________________
Pistachio Milk Cake:  Flavor was everything. Think pistachio tres leche. It was SLIGHTLY too moist, even for what it is - did NOT take from the experience though.

Yemen Chocolate:  Cute little gold dust on top, the price is more than fair considering it’s literally “Dubai Chocolate” - which I don’t enjoy because of the texture. The chocolate was of great quality, the pistachios were shaved into what reminds me of fried rice noodles. If you like Dubai Chocolate, you’ll enjoy. 😊

Triple Chocolate Cake:  DECADENNNTT. Top tier quality! I keep referring to quality but this place exudes it - made even more surprising bc it’s a chain. ⛓️‍💥 It isn’t huge, but because of    its richness, can be shared between ~2-3 of even the largest fatties! Velvety smooth,  thick mousse meets perfectly balanced, light and yet dense, sponge cake - Signed, sealed, & delivered in an exquisitely, complementary dark chocolate coating.

Chocolate Cappuccino Cake:  Needs work.
The cake was too dense and very dry. The icing was slightly “crusty” - not enough moisture and the flavor was missing that rich espresso flavor. It could have been stale, but I think it’s more likely that the recipe is struggling to retain moisture because it’s vegan.

All in all - will be back. I don’t even like sweets, but I’m committed now & am excited to try the desserts that pay homage to the Yemen culture! 😊

I absolutely LOVE Qahwah House: the vibrant atmosphere, well designed interior - we loved sitting on the sofa with moveable arm rests that lined the back wall, beautiful servers and baristas. It was so nice to meet the cheerful owner Sulaiman!

As someone with a dairy allergy I was so surprised to see they had vegan chocolate cake (made with almond and coconut milk). My friend and I came for dessert - I ordered the chocolate cake and he got the pistachio dream dessert and a cold Mofawar latte (with a dash of fragrant cardamom). We both greatly enjoyed what we ordered.

Another time I came and got their delicious peppermint tea. Highly recommend their tea, coffee, and desserts/pastries!
